Class oracle.mapviewer.share.stylex.HeatMapStyleModel extends AbstractStyleModel implements Serializable

Serialized Fields

colorStops

java.awt.Color[] colorStops
Color gradient. Always from lowest intensity to highest

numSteps

int numSteps
Steps between all color stops (default is 200 )

alpha

int alpha
Opacity of the heat map; from 0 - 255 inclusive

spotLightRadius

SizeDefinition spotLightRadius
Spot light radius.

containerThemeName

java.lang.String containerThemeName
This theme serves as the boundary for the heat map graphics (so that no area outside the container theme will be rendered by the heat map). This must be a theme in the same schema as the heat map style. For instance, if the heat map is generated for all the starbucks shops within USA, then the container theme should be a polygon theme that represents the USA.

gridSampleFactor

double gridSampleFactor
This parameter controls how to sample the device window down to the internal data grid used for heat map calculation. The device window width and height will be divided by this value, and the result will be the size of the data grid.
